      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Procure Materials and Services (Direct &amp; Indirect)
Process: PM-040-090 Certify Suppliers for Quality Programs
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-2DA76808-C787-4DE5-9A87-B962B64E2464" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Apply qualification standards  agreed upon for this purchasing relationship to each candidate supplier. Attempt to determine the supplier's capability to manufacture and distribute quality product. Which meets company need. Consider QS 9000 Certification, market share, D&amp;B rating. Supplier's production capacity, supplier location, supplier distribution, ability to provide technical support, loyalty to company.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-C8FFED5B-0905-4E69-89BB-2F7CE5496DA0" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Approval process is defined by commodity.  Ex:  For all manufacturing related items, Approved xCCB whitepaper or PRQ
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-C16BB1A3-2EC5-43B0-9EE1-32042D2900A8" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Boundary apps
•MQCS (Materials Quality Certification System.  IAPM# 1086)
•GSAT (GSC Supplier Assessment Tool.  IAPM#  9069)
•CIRA (Certification &amp; Integrated Risk Assessment.  IAPM# 16801)
•SPEED</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-AA59E239-8D12-45A6-8EF3-10CEEDECF043" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Doc Locator specification:
*Supplier Selection Process Specification  (DL-0002375.pdf)
*Supply Chain Supplier Qualification (DL-0002403.pdf</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-013052EA-4710-4B92-BB36-368BD53354C6" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Dhanwantry, Kalyan R &lt;kalyan.r.dhanwantry@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
